SIMPLE: loud
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Loud
<hw>Loud</hw> <pr>(loud)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Louder</adjf> <pr>(loud"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Loudest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>loud</ets>,
<ets>lud</ets>, AS. <ets>hl⟦umac⟧d</ets>; akin to OS.
<ets>hl⟦umac⟧d</ets>, D. <ets>luid</ets>, OHG. <ets>l⟦umac⟧t</ets>, G.
<ets>laut</ets>, L. <ets>-clutus</ets>, in in<ets>clutus</ets>,
in<ets>clitus</ets>, celebrated, renowned, <ets>cluere</ets> to be
called, Gr. <grk>klyto`s</grk> heard, loud, famous, <grk>kly`ein</grk>
to hear, Skr. <ets>⟦cced⟧ru</ets>. ⟦root⟧41. Cf. <er>Client</er>,
<er>Listen</er>, <er>Slave</er> a serf.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having,
making, or being a strong or great sound; noisy; striking the ear with
great force; <as>as, a <ex>loud</ex> cry; <ex>loud</ex>
thunder.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They were instant with <qex>loud</qex> voices, requiring that he
might be crucified.</q> <rj><qau>Luke xxiii. 23.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Clamorous; boisterous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She is <qex>loud</qex> and stubborn.</q> <rj><qau>Prov. vii.
11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Emphatic; impressive; urgent; <as>as, a
<ex>loud</ex> call for united effort</as>.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Ostentatious; likely to attract attention; gaudy;
<as>as, a <ex>loud</ex> style of dress; <ex>loud</ex> colors.</as></def>
<mark>[Slang]</mark></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Noisy; boisterous; vociferous; clamorous;
obstreperous; turbulent; blustering; vehement.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loud</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Loud
<hw>Loud</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>hl⟦umac⟧de</ets>.]</ety>
<def>With loudness; loudly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To speak <qex>loud</qex> in public assemblies.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Loudful</ent>⟦br⟧
